    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <p>The International Reform Federation was a social reform organization within the Methodist Church concerned with the promotion of temperance and peace. The organization was founded by Wilbur F. Crafts.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <p>The record group consists of cashbooks and a financial ledger (on microfilm) and a scattering of original materials, including correspondence, minutes of annual meetings, appointment books and newspaper clippings.</p>
    </scopecontent>
